<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="879" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="67.[160,1155,143,202]" pageId="67" pageNumber="879">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,292,143,167]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="879">Etymology.</emphasis>
The island of Great Nicobar, the 
<typeStatus box="[677,727,143,167]" pageId="67" pageNumber="879">type</typeStatus>
locality of this species is the basis for this name. The name is treated as an adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="879" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="67.[160,1155,247,340]" pageId="67" pageNumber="879">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,283,247,271]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="879">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is different from all other species in having the following combination of character states: short IOS, dense pilosity, a long central keel, mesoscutellum semicircular and metascutellum visible.
</paragraph>
